## <a id="1-3-0"></a> v1.3.0

**Release Date: October 1, 2021**

**1.3.0** represents the fourth minor GA release of Tanzu Build Service.

This release includes a few notable new features:

* Support for [cosign image signing](https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/blob/main/docs/image.md#cosign-config) for images built with TBS
* Support for [kubernetes service bindings](https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/blob/main/docs/servicebindings.md)
* Support for creating CustomStacks for UBI images
* Image resources can specify [additional tags](https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/blob/main/docs/image.md#-configuring-tags) that will be written to.
* Builds can use registries for caching instead of volumes – see [image config](https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/blob/main/docs/image.md) for how to set the cache tag to be used
* New kpack v1alpha2 build api – notable changes can be found [here](https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/releases/tag/v0.4.0)

### Breaking Changes

* Installation has changed, see installation docs for new process using `imgpkg`

### Product Snapshot

Tanzu Build Service 1.3.0 ships with the following components:

* [kpack 0.4.0](https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/releases/tag/v0.4.0)
* [kpack cli v0.4.0](https://github.com/vmware-tanzu/kpack-cli/releases/tag/v0.4.0)
* [CNB lifecycle v0.11.4](https://github.com/buildpacks/lifecycle/releases/tag/v0.11.4)
* [Stacks Operator v0.0.7](https://github.com/pivotal/stacks-operator/releases/tag/v0.0.7)

Tanzu Build Service supports and utilizes [Tanzu Buildpacks](https://docs.pivotal.io/tanzu-buildpacks).

### Product Dependencies

Build Service can be installed on any Kubernetes cluster (v1.19 or later).

### Upgrade Path

v1.2.* can be upgraded to v1.3.*. Please follow the [install](installing.html) process to upgrade.
